node.text:
A tutorial for my 5 minute face using the @ecotools BioBlender makeup sponge! If I only have 5 minutes (which is more often than not) I like to focus on my skin! The BioBlender is super soft and bouncy and creates a gorgeous, seamless look! The 4 edge design is so versatile, it’s eco-friendly, and affordable!! Link below to shop at @Walmart! #ad

Shop BioBlender here! https://bit.ly/3k3KOjY

node.text:
Here are a few healthy suhoor ideas that will hopefully get you through the end of Ramadan! •

Mini Omelet Bites: 
modified from this recipe: https://www.wellplated.com/healthy-br...
(I used a mini muffin tin rather than the larger 12 cup , so took only 15 minutes to bake) •

Chocolate Chia Seed Pudding: 
2 tbsp cacao powder , or cocoa powder
3 tbsp maple syrup
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup dairy-free milk
1/4 cup chia seeds 
garnish with berries or nuts!

No Bake Energy Bars:
13-14 medium medjool pitted dates (about 1 1/2 cups)
1 cup raw walnuts
1 cup old fashioned rolled oats 
1/4 cup peanut butter 
1/4 cup flax seed powder (optional to add fiber)
1/4 cup unsweetened coconut flakes 
3 tbsp cacao or cocoa powder
1/4 tsp salt

Green Smoothie:
1 frozen banana
1/2 cup frozen mango
1 cup fresh spinach
fresh ginger (size of end of finger)
squeeze of half a lime 
coconut water (or just plain water!) to desired consistency

1 bunch asparagus 
Season with: 
garlic salt
black pepper
rosemary 
olive oil

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by LEENA SNOUBAR on August 11, 2021 tagging @omarsnoubar, @inayacphoto, and @lushra. May be an image of 2 people, child, cake, indoor and text that says 'Alainas sit birthday'.

node.text: Alaina’s birthday party was a success 🥰 not only did we celebrate our princess but we also celebrated making it through one year of parenthood for Omar and I because this stuff is HARD! We made it through the sleepless nights, adjusted to our new roles, supported each other when we felt like we were at our breaking point. Our lives changed (for the better) forever last August and thank God we made it! May God protect all of our children make them healthy and happy always!!! Ameen! That’s truly all that matters 💗💗💗

node.text: And just like that, my baby is one. I pray God protects you and gives you health and blesses you with the best in this life and hereafter 💗 I cried so many times making this video 😭 She will always be my baby!! Happy first birthday Alaina Noor! ✨

node.text: I’m such a different mother than I thought I would be. When I was pregnant I had this idea that I was going to be super scheduled, Alaina was going to be sleeping in her own room by 6 months, we would have a perfect routine down everyday. Once she arrived, I realized she was only little for such a short time. I threw sleep training and everything they said to do out the window and enjoyed rocking her to sleep and now she even sleeps next to me all night and I wouldn’t change a thing 💗 Our days aren’t as structured as I had envisioned, but they are filled with more joy than I could have ever imagined. I’m so grateful to be her Mama ✨ If you’re a mom or soon-to-be mama, don’t feel guilty for doing what is best for your family and for your own mental health even if it’s not what everyone else is doing 💗

node.text:
I want to always remember these sweet baby hands 💗 Wanted to share a few travel must-haves with a baby! I have a whole blog post on this if you need a packing list for baby!

1. Travel stroller: the first time we traveled with our baby I almost didn’t bring it but OMG it’s the number 1 essential! This will save your back and they can also take naps in it when you’re on the go. We use the Doona stroller/car seat! 

2. Teething crackers: helps keep them entertained on flights 

3. Portable sound machine: drowns out noise if they are sleeping in the same room as you or out in public in the stroller 

4. Baby sunscreen: do you have any fave brands?

5. Disposable changing pads: (puppy pads for dogs or chux pads in hospital 😂) best hack for changing diapers in dirty public areas/planes!
